  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "In the TV series \"Game of Thrones,\" the Night King transforms human children into White Walkers, but the specifics of their growth and aging process are not explicitly detailed in the show. What is clear from the series is that the Night King has the ability to convert human infants into White Walkers, as seen in Season 4, Episode 4 (\"Oathkeeper\"). The transformation process involves touching the child, which causes their eyes to turn blue, marking their conversion.\n\nWhen it comes to the White Walkers seen in later episodes, they appear to be fully grown, but the show does not explain whether they grow to adulthood immediately after the transformation or if they age naturally over time. Therefore, while it is evident that the children are transformed into White Walkers, the exact mechanics of their aging are left ambiguous in the narrative of the series.",
